ce:caption.ce:simple-para:
The HOMO, LUMO energy levels, the energy gap (ΔE

                        HOMO-LUMO
                     ), and the distribution of the HOMO and LUMO orbitals of the optimized modeled structures of (A) graphene oxide and (B) the N-GQDs.

ce:section.ce:para:
In this figure, the HOMO and LUMO molecular orbitals of the graphene oxide profile are determined. According to the HOMO LUMO energy levels of the structures, it was possible to compare the HOMO and LUMO orbitals, which take part in the ET-process in graphene oxide and N-GQDs. The calculated energy gap of HOMO-LUMO (ΔE

                        HOMO-LUMO
                     ) of the graphene oxide and N-GQDs profiles were found to be equal to 5.41 and 4.36 eV, respectively. The stability of the hardness level and electron donor features are represented with Δη factor (inherently minus amount in the scale of eV). The main path of the ET-process is that the HOMO of the other molecules accepts the electron from the excited state of the graphene oxide and/or N-GQDs.
